name: ImageIO
description: Imageio is a Python library that provides an easy interface to read and write a wide range of image data, including animated images, volumetric data, and scientific formats. It is cross-platform, runs on Python 3.6+, and is easy to install.
description_good_justification: Website and Documentation lives here: https://imageio.readthedocs.io/en/stable/
contribution_justification:
The contribution workflow is PR based with a mandatory review by at least 1 member, CI and coverage tests.
Entrypoint to get started contributing: https://github.com/imageio/imageio#contributing

floss_license_justification: The BSD-2-Clause license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
floss_license_osi_justification: The BSD-2-Clause license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
documentation_basics_justification: Documentation lives here: https://imageio.readthedocs.io/en/stable/index.html
repo_public_justification: Repository on GitHub, which provides public git repositories with URLs.
repo_track_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git can track the changes, who made them, and when they were made.
repo_interim_justification: The repo includes ALL code (100% open source) and interrim versions are available in PR branches and the master branch.
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_tags_justification: Releases have a git tag and their commit message begins with "REL:"
release_notes_justification:
We maintain a changelog that includes links to the issues and PRs that lead to relevant changes being made.
Changelog lives here: https://github.com/imageio/imageio/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md
report_responses_justification: Not sure if GH provides neat summary statistics for this point, but you can inspect the typical response time on known/confirmed bugs: https://github.com/imageio/imageio/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen+label%3A%22type%3A+bug%22
enhancement_responses_justification:
Not sure if GH provides neat summary statistics for this point, but you can inspect the typical response time on enhancements:
https://github.com/imageio/imageio/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen+label%3A%22type%3A+enhancement%22
build_common_tools_justification: the software itself is pure python. supportive tooling is based on commonly used projects (sphinx, pytest, coverage, ...)
test_justification: GH Actions handles all CI. Further, testing is done via pytest following the standard workflow.
test_most_justification: coverage is currently at around 87% and is being monitored in every PR
test_policy_justification: our CI tests for coverage including any newly added code. In general, we require near-total coverage of enhancements before a merge.
tests_are_added_justification: Not sure if there are neat summary statistics to show this. Recent changes (and their test/coverage implications) can be found in the list of recently closed PRs: https://github.com/imageio/imageio/pulls?q=is%3Apr+is%3Aclosed
warnings_justification: there is no compiler in python. We do enforce code quality though via linting tests during a PR (flake8 + black). Any test-discovered warnings introduced by a PR are handled during that PR.
warnings_fixed_justification: warnings discovered during testing are handled during the PR.
warnings_strict_justification: warnings discovered during testing are handled during the PR.
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests.
english_justification: Documentation can be found at the links shared above. Bug reports and comments are handled via GH issues: https://github.com/imageio/imageio/issues

maintained_justification: At the time of this writing there are three people actively maintaining the project while others are occasional contributors.
